963
01:11:30,180 --> 01:11:33,100
Honey, just wait a second, will you?

964
01:11:36,340 --> 01:11:39,780
- Danny!
- Honey, l had no choice.

965
01:11:39,980 --> 01:11:43,820
It was an emergancy, she wasn't going to bring him back
till she got what she wanted.

966
01:11:44,020 --> 01:11:46,460
You mean until she got what you wanted.

967
01:11:46,660 --> 01:11:48,860
Honey, it's not like that.

968
01:11:49,900 --> 01:11:54,420
Look, Uncle Joe and l, we talked.
l mean, we really talked.

969
01:11:54,620 --> 01:11:57,980
He's been in Washington.
Some military contract.

970
01:11:58,180 --> 01:12:03,380
- Oh, yeah?
- I brought him back today and
we're going to go and see his attorneys.

971
01:12:03,580 --> 01:12:06,900
From now on, honey,
l'm going to be responsible for him.

972
01:12:07,100 --> 01:12:11,220
l'm gonna be here with him,
and...you know.

973
01:12:14,260 --> 01:12:16,220
Rich.

974
01:12:17,660 --> 01:12:21,300
- What about your cousins, you made deal?
- My cousins are animals!

975
01:12:21,500 --> 01:12:24,300
They would put him in a home
if they could.

976
01:12:24,500 --> 01:12:26,660
l'll take care of their children,

977
01:12:26,860 --> 01:12:30,180
you know, give each kid
like a scholarship or something,

978
01:12:30,380 --> 01:12:32,740
but my cousins forget it, don't deserve anything.

979
01:12:32,940 --> 01:12:35,980
- You bastard!
- Frank what are you doing?
- Frank, no!

980
01:12:36,180 --> 01:12:39,340
- Whatever happened to ''Hello''?
- We heard every word.

981
01:12:39,540 --> 01:12:41,900
- What did you do? Listen outside my door?
- Always.

982
01:12:42,100 --> 01:12:46,180
- l had no idea how sick you guys were.
- Come spend a day with us.

983
01:12:46,380 --> 01:12:49,180
- l'd rather shove this up my ass.
- l'll do it.

984
01:12:49,380 --> 01:12:55,420
- You're playing a lone hand, huh? Are you double crossing us?
- First of all, l never agreed to anything with you.

985
01:12:56,300 --> 01:12:59,340
l only said was I'll visit my uncle, see
how things were and let me tell u something.

986
01:12:59,540 --> 01:13:02,060
l saw, and it made me sick.

987
01:13:02,260 --> 01:13:07,700
- You bastard.
- l like it better when she said that. I think it's the accent or something.

988
01:13:07,900 --> 01:13:11,060
- l thought l'd find you here together.
- We're not all together.

989
01:13:11,260 --> 01:13:13,220
Right.

990
01:13:14,740 --> 01:13:18,100
Do you know, l thought
you were different than the others.

991
01:13:18,300 --> 01:13:20,540
But you're no different, you're exactly the same.

992
01:13:20,740 --> 01:13:24,420
l am looking out for my uncle, OK?
l am looking out for his welfare.

993
01:13:24,620 --> 01:13:27,580
Bullshit. They were willing
to wait until he died.

994
01:13:27,780 --> 01:13:29,860
But not you, you're going to eat him raw.

995
01:13:30,060 --> 01:13:33,900
- Wait a minute. Danny is not like that.
- Try to remember something, OK?

996
01:13:34,100 --> 01:13:36,460
ln the long run, nobody likes a tease.

997
01:13:36,660 --> 01:13:40,700
You are a cheap,
chiselling, low-life hustler.

998
01:13:40,900 --> 01:13:44,300
- [Carl] You said it!
- Well, it takes one to spot one.

999
01:13:49,940 --> 01:13:51,700
- Stop it!
- Great!

1000
01:13:51,900 --> 01:13:55,820
Now you stop it,
after she gets in a shot.

1001
01:13:56,940 --> 01:14:01,940
l'll give you half a million dollars to leave.
Cash. Soon as l get the money.

1002
01:14:02,140 --> 01:14:04,940
Better than delivering pizza,
even in a good year.

1003
01:14:05,140 --> 01:14:10,060
She gets half a million dollars and we get a couple
of lousy scholarships? That's not fair!

1004
01:14:10,260 --> 01:14:14,060
No, l will give you half a million dollars
and you leave.

1005
01:14:14,260 --> 01:14:17,300
You'll give me half a million?
l'm getting it all!

1006
01:14:17,500 --> 01:14:21,140
He sees right through you.
You're a walking fish-tank, baby.

1007
01:14:21,340 --> 01:14:25,060
- You and your tan tushy can...
- l'll sleep with him.

1008
01:14:26,380 --> 01:14:28,540
What?

1009
01:14:28,780 --> 01:14:33,660
- What, you're...you're gonna...?
- As soon as he gets back from work.

1010
01:14:33,900 --> 01:14:36,460
l'll give him a right good one.

1011
01:14:37,620 --> 01:14:39,740
You... See, it wouldn't...

1012
01:14:39,980 --> 01:14:43,660
He wouldn't be interested in that.
lt wouldn't even matter.

1013
01:14:43,900 --> 01:14:47,500
lt'll matter. l'll make it matter.

1014
01:14:55,780 --> 01:14:57,540
# Inka dinka doo #

1015
01:14:59,900 --> 01:15:01,780
Molly.

1016
01:15:02,020 --> 01:15:05,540
Do you know that both of my daughters
are named Molly?

1017
01:15:05,780 --> 01:15:07,860
Oh, God.

1018
01:15:08,100 --> 01:15:10,060
Oh, God.

1019
01:15:14,060 --> 01:15:17,620
Oh, God. You think she'll do it?

1020
01:15:18,860 --> 01:15:20,020
Yes, l do.

1021
01:15:20,260 --> 01:15:23,980
You've given her no choice.
She'll do it just to beat you.

1022
01:15:24,220 --> 01:15:27,980
Oh, Jesus. You think it'll work?

1023
01:15:29,580 --> 01:15:31,940
A young girl with a body like that?

1024
01:15:32,140 --> 01:15:36,340
There'll be nothing left of him
but a smile and an old hat.

1025
01:15:49,540 --> 01:15:51,980
Welcome home, Joe.

1026
01:15:56,540 --> 01:15:58,500
Hello, Molly.

1027
01:16:02,540 --> 01:16:04,500
[inaudible]

1028
01:16:05,220 --> 01:16:07,900
l'm tired. l'm going upstairs.

1029
01:16:09,740 --> 01:16:10,700
Uncle Joe!

1030
01:16:15,780 --> 01:16:16,740
Wait!

1031
01:16:16,940 --> 01:16:19,540
Sir, will you need my assistance?

1032
01:16:19,740 --> 01:16:22,980
No, Molly will assist me.

1033
01:16:24,180 --> 01:16:26,700
Oh, l see. Very good, sir.

1034
01:16:27,860 --> 01:16:30,060
Let's go.

1035
01:16:34,460 --> 01:16:38,420
Sir? May l ask for a reference
before you go upstairs?

1036
01:16:38,620 --> 01:16:40,620
Not now, Douglas.

1037
01:16:44,540 --> 01:16:47,220
Goodbye, sir.

1038
01:16:47,420 --> 01:16:50,260
Uncle Joe, wait! Please wait.

1039
01:16:50,460 --> 01:16:54,660
- l have a surprise for you.
- Danny, don't.

1040
01:16:57,380 --> 01:16:58,420
Up we go.

1041
01:17:01,700 --> 01:17:04,260
His face! Did you see it?

1042
01:17:04,460 --> 01:17:07,220
l've never been in one of these before.

1043
01:17:08,180 --> 01:17:09,660
[Uncle Joe] Hang on!

1044
01:17:16,340 --> 01:17:18,500
Molly, let me say something.

1045
01:17:18,700 --> 01:17:22,340
No. Don't say anything.

1046
01:17:23,860 --> 01:17:27,860
- A little young for you, ain't she, Joe?
- Who's there?

1047
01:17:31,980 --> 01:17:34,060
Hi, Joe. lt's been a long time.

1048
01:17:35,020 --> 01:17:38,980
- lt's Daniel.
- Daniel?

1049
01:17:42,740 --> 01:17:48,620
- What are you...? You got so old.
- You're no Monet yourself.

1050
01:17:51,260 --> 01:17:54,540
Molly, this is my cousin Daniel.
Danny's father.

1051
01:17:56,100 --> 01:17:59,500
Danny asked me to come.
He's got a real regard for you.

1052
01:17:59,700 --> 01:18:04,900
He made me think that maybe things
are different than the way l remember them.

1053
01:18:05,100 --> 01:18:08,540
But they're not, are they?
lt's still the same.

1054
01:18:08,740 --> 01:18:13,060
God, this place still stinks from greed.

1055
01:18:13,260 --> 01:18:15,540
Those who have it...

1056
01:18:16,660 --> 01:18:18,780
and those who want it.

1057
01:18:25,940 --> 01:18:27,380
Dad!

1058
01:18:28,620 --> 01:18:33,500
- Hello, Daniel.
- You came! That was great of you.

1059
01:18:34,460 --> 01:18:36,700
- l'm leaving.
- What?

1060
01:18:36,900 --> 01:18:39,780
God. They're all still here.

1061
01:18:39,980 --> 01:18:44,660
First your parents, now you. He'll outlive
your children and leave them nothing.

1062
01:18:44,860 --> 01:18:46,380
You wanna lighten up?

1063
01:18:46,580 --> 01:18:50,740
You know who ruins this world?
The greedy. That's it.

1064
01:18:52,060 --> 01:18:55,580
They have it. l want it.
l have it. l want more.

1065
01:18:55,780 --> 01:18:58,980
That's the real pollution. Greed.

1066
01:19:01,420 --> 01:19:03,740
You know who l think ruins the world?

1067
01:19:03,940 --> 01:19:09,180
Pompous, self-righteous, holier-than-thou
middle-aged fanatics in pony-tails

1068
01:19:09,380 --> 01:19:12,180
who give away their kids' toys!

1069
01:19:14,460 --> 01:19:17,940
- He's got you too, huh?
- No, he doesn't have me.

1070
01:19:18,140 --> 01:19:21,340
- Can't the truth be in between?
- No!

1071
01:19:21,540 --> 01:19:24,220
One way is all right,
one way is all wrong.

1072
01:19:24,420 --> 01:19:26,700
His way or my way. Pick.

1073
01:19:26,900 --> 01:19:28,220
- Dad.
- Pick!

1074
01:19:33,260 --> 01:19:35,500
- You are just so...
- Pick!

1075
01:19:38,820 --> 01:19:41,500
All right, then l pick him.

1076
01:19:43,940 --> 01:19:47,740
At least he doesn't take himself
so goddamn seriously.

1077
01:20:17,500 --> 01:20:19,380
l'm leaving.

1078
01:20:21,180 --> 01:20:23,100
Why?

1079
01:20:24,180 --> 01:20:29,220
l can't believe l was almost
going to screw the old boy for money.

1080
01:20:30,380 --> 01:20:33,820
l suppose maybe l've always
been here for the money.

1081
01:20:34,020 --> 01:20:36,780
Christ, l make myself sick.

1082
01:20:36,980 --> 01:20:39,220
l have to get out of here.

1083
01:20:40,380 --> 01:20:41,900
l understand.

1084
01:20:43,500 --> 01:20:46,500
You'll take care of him, won't you?

1085
01:20:47,220 --> 01:20:48,900
Of course.

1086
01:20:49,100 --> 01:20:52,820
You're not going to put him in a home?

1087
01:20:53,020 --> 01:20:54,060
Never.

1088
01:20:57,540 --> 01:20:59,380
Bye.

1089
01:21:12,260 --> 01:21:14,700
Hey. You OK?

1090
01:21:16,260 --> 01:21:17,380
Yeah.

1091
01:21:18,540 --> 01:21:22,980
God, that was some scene
with your father. l just...

1092
01:21:25,700 --> 01:21:27,060
What?

1093
01:21:28,980 --> 01:21:30,660
That wasn't my father.

1094
01:21:32,820 --> 01:21:35,260
What?

1095
01:21:35,460 --> 01:21:39,860
That was an actor.
My father wouldn't come here on a bet.

1096
01:21:42,380 --> 01:21:45,220
- So you just...?
- lt was my only shot, honey.

1097
01:21:45,420 --> 01:21:48,900
He wanted me to pick him over my father.

1098
01:21:49,100 --> 01:21:51,660
Yes, and you said you never would.

1099
01:21:51,860 --> 01:21:55,540
l didn't. l picked him over an actor.

1100
01:21:57,780 --> 01:22:00,100
- Don't touch me.
- What?

1101
01:22:00,300 --> 01:22:03,260
- Hey. Come on. What's the matter?
- Danny.

1102
01:22:03,460 --> 01:22:06,500
You dropped your compass in the woods
and you're lost.

1103
01:22:06,700 --> 01:22:08,260
l'm not lost.

1104
01:22:08,500 --> 01:22:12,660
- You don't see how sick this is?
- No!

1105
01:22:12,900 --> 01:22:17,740
- Who got hurt?
- The truth got hurt. OK?

1106
01:22:17,980 --> 01:22:21,780
lntegrity, self-respect,
decent human behaviour got hurt.

1107
01:22:22,020 --> 01:22:25,980
l will be good to him.
Tell me who else will be as good.

1108
01:22:26,180 --> 01:22:29,540
- That's not the point.
- No, that is the point.

1109
01:22:30,740 --> 01:22:35,020
We've been through a lot together
and l think l've been pretty loyal.

1110
01:22:35,260 --> 01:22:37,620
Honey, you've been great.

1111
01:22:37,860 --> 01:22:42,620
But if you touch one cent
of your uncle's money, we're through.

1112
01:22:44,180 --> 01:22:46,420
- What are you, crazy?
- l mean it.

1113
01:22:46,660 --> 01:22:51,100
lf you take any of that money,
l will have no respect for you.

1114
01:22:51,340 --> 01:22:54,740
Jesus! You sound like my father.

1115
01:22:54,980 --> 01:22:59,500
No, l sound like the actor
who played your father. Enjoy your money.

1116
01:23:05,860 --> 01:23:08,060
- Daniel McTeague Junior.
- Here.

1117
01:23:12,340 --> 01:23:16,020
Your great-uncle has chosen,
for reasons l assume he's explained,

1118
01:23:16,260 --> 01:23:18,300
to transfer to you all his assets,

1119
01:23:18,540 --> 01:23:23,540
including full control of his commercial,
personal and financial affairs.

1120
01:23:23,780 --> 01:23:26,500
My boy. My good boy.

1121
01:23:27,620 --> 01:23:32,540
l would like to give you a full picture
of your great-uncle's holdings.

1122
01:23:32,740 --> 01:23:36,860
The McTeague Scrap Metal Company,
comprising scrapyards, trucking...

1123
01:23:37,100 --> 01:23:38,660
Excuse me.

1124
01:23:40,580 --> 01:23:44,700
Uncle Joe, there's something
l'd like to explain to you.

1125
01:23:46,580 --> 01:23:50,420
First of all, when l came
to your birthday party that time,

1126
01:23:50,620 --> 01:23:55,740
l had no idea this was going to happen.
l wasn't after your money.

1127
01:23:55,940 --> 01:23:59,700
l know that. That's why l love you.

1128
01:24:05,100 --> 01:24:07,860
Joe. l have to tell you something.

1129
01:24:08,060 --> 01:24:09,380
What?

1130
01:24:11,220 --> 01:24:12,700
l'm...

1131
01:24:14,180 --> 01:24:17,020
going to take such good care of you.

1132
01:24:19,020 --> 01:24:21,220
You're a good boy.

1133
01:24:22,420 --> 01:24:24,500
ls that it?

1134
01:24:25,380 --> 01:24:27,820
- Yeah.
- Well, that was lovely.

1135
01:24:28,500 --> 01:24:32,660
As l was saying, the McTeague
Scrap Metal Company, comprising...

1136
01:24:32,860 --> 01:24:37,420
- Stop! Sign nothing!
- What the hell is this?

1137
01:24:37,620 --> 01:24:40,540
Oh, my, my, my.

1138
01:24:40,740 --> 01:24:43,100
lf deceit has a name, it's his name!

1139
01:24:48,700 --> 01:24:54,020
Daniel, is it true? ls everything
these gerbils have been telling me true?

1140
01:24:57,900 --> 01:24:59,860
Dad.

1141
01:25:00,060 --> 01:25:01,020
Dad?

1142
01:25:01,220 --> 01:25:04,660
Yes, Dad. Daniel McTeague Senior, his father.

1143
01:25:04,860 --> 01:25:09,660
His real father, not the actor he hired
to come to your house last night.

1144
01:25:10,700 --> 01:25:12,460
Danny.

1145
01:25:15,300 --> 01:25:17,780
They told me that, Daniel.

1146
01:25:20,420 --> 01:25:22,300
ls it true?

1147
01:25:24,020 --> 01:25:26,380
Yeah. lt's true.

1148
01:25:28,580 --> 01:25:34,860
You hired an actor to pretend he was me,
and then pretended to fight with him?

1149
01:25:35,060 --> 01:25:38,660
And told him
you preferred Uncle Joe to me?

1150
01:25:38,860 --> 01:25:42,500
Well, when you put it like that,
it sounds kind of bad.

1151
01:25:42,700 --> 01:25:47,340
l know we've had our differences.
And l know you think l'm strange.

1152
01:25:47,540 --> 01:25:49,420
No. No, Dad.

1153
01:25:49,620 --> 01:25:53,300
l am. But l've always respected you,
Daniel. Always.

1154
01:25:53,500 --> 01:25:56,300
l've always felt you had real character.

1155
01:25:56,500 --> 01:25:57,700
Ha-ha!

1156
01:26:00,500 --> 01:26:03,100
- Does money mean this much to you?
- No.

1157
01:26:03,300 --> 01:26:06,260
l didn't go and see Uncle Joe
for the money.

1158
01:26:06,460 --> 01:26:11,780
We made a deal. lf he kept the money
in the family, he'd get a cut. Right?

1159
01:26:11,980 --> 01:26:14,420
- Yes, but...
- Then he double-crossed us.

1160
01:26:14,620 --> 01:26:17,580
Because they're scum! They're greedy!

1161
01:26:17,780 --> 01:26:21,140
We're greedy? We were willing to share.

1162
01:26:22,260 --> 01:26:23,780
Dad.

1163
01:26:24,820 --> 01:26:30,020
l don't know what happened.
l just got...sucked in.

1164
01:26:30,220 --> 01:26:34,260
First one thing didn't seem wrong,
then another, until...

1165
01:26:34,460 --> 01:26:36,780
Nothing seemed wrong.

1166
01:26:36,980 --> 01:26:39,780
l know. That's why l left.

1167
01:26:53,420 --> 01:26:57,300
- How are you, Joe?
- l'm still eating grapes.

1168
01:27:19,860 --> 01:27:22,820
- Uncle Joe.
- Save it.

1169
01:27:24,220 --> 01:27:29,380
OK, Joe. Bare knuckles, toe to toe.
We've spent 20 years eating your shit

1170
01:27:29,580 --> 01:27:33,500
and saying, ''Mm! Delicious.. what a cook.''
No more. We've hired attorneys.

1171
01:27:33,700 --> 01:27:37,220
lf we don't get our share,
we'll get you declared incompetent.

1172
01:27:37,420 --> 01:27:39,940
And we'll win,
because we found out things.

1173
01:27:40,140 --> 01:27:43,100
You've got toys in the attic. Broken toys.

1174
01:27:43,780 --> 01:27:47,780
And we'll hammer on you
until you cave in. Understand?

1175
01:27:47,980 --> 01:27:51,100
- Or is your mind already gone?
- All right!

1176
01:27:54,220 --> 01:27:56,780
Sit down. All of you.

1177
01:27:57,860 --> 01:27:59,620
- Uncle Joe...
- Quiet.

1178
01:28:09,940 --> 01:28:11,860
Go ahead.

1179
01:28:12,060 --> 01:28:15,100
As l was about to say before the circus came to town,

1180
01:28:15,300 --> 01:28:17,380
your uncle's holdings at their peak

